@Firetoad pathing units is a bigger problem than having units, so as long as they're not moving you can save some effort. if units are crossing the map, try and keep them spread out while they travel (e.g. set up your own custom navgrid and send them to random offsets from the navgrid). Otherwise units can get trapped on corners and create pathing lag even when there's no combat happening get rid of auras (which have to check for additions/removals every frame), and instead create your own pseudo-auras (which only check every second or so)

function Battle( keys ) local caster = keys.caster local target = keys.target local ability = keys.ability global_target = keys.target local duration = ability:GetSpecialValueFor("duration") if not target:TriggerSpellAbsorb(ability) then target:SetForceAttackTarget(caster) local order2 = { UnitIndex = target:entindex(), OrderType = DOTA_UNIT_ORDER_ATTACK_TARGET, TargetIndex = caster:entindex() } ExecuteOrderFromTable(order2) caster:AddNewModifier(caster, ability, "modifier_silenced_and_muted", {duration = duration}) caster:AddNewModifier(caster, ability, "modifier_check_fort", {duration = duration}) target:AddNewModifier(caster, ability, "modifier_silenced_and_muted", {duration = duration}) target:AddNewModifier(caster, ability, "modifier_check_fort", {duration = duration}) caster:SetForceAttackTarget(target) local order = { UnitIndex = caster:entindex(), OrderType = DOTA_UNIT_ORDER_ATTACK_TARGET, TargetIndex = target:entindex() } ExecuteOrderFromTable(order) EmitSoundOn("Steam_Trade", target) end end
